## Context
Reviewer 2 (general + linear) + Reviewer 1 other comments: replace abstract /
declarative passages with concrete actors, sites, instruments, dates, and
consequences.

## Actions (passage-level, R2 list)
- Development-economics section: how economic reasoning entered negotiations; name actors/institutions/mechanisms; name the OECD development economists.
- Clarify: models-vs-accounting-infrastructure opposition (really IAMs vs DAC measurement, p3); "longer trajectory of climate economics" intention (p3).
- Why borrowing the aid reporting system is problematic (consequences + who drove it).
- Article 4.3 "transactional language" sentence; "rigorous incremental-cost framework" (concrete); when/why it was abandoned vs extended; welfare-theoretic-transfers sentence (p8).
- p8 "the need for a broader category arose" — provide evidence/examples (R2p).
- Bali Action Plan: beyond the gloss in 0140, explain what changed institutionally/politically between Article 4.3 and Decision 1/CP.13, and what triggered the shift (R2w substantive).
- CDM functioning; "concept later migrated" (examples); "carbon accounting not financial accounting" (substantiate); who generated post-2012 demand.
- p12 "political legitimacy" introduced suddenly — say why it becomes a concern at this stage and for whom (R2x).
- UNFCCC-2007 + Stern Review "created the conditions for a new kind of economic object" — claim too strong as stated; demonstrate carefully or soften (R2y).
- "an economic object… that required not just models but accounting infrastructure" (p12) — too abstract; specify concretely (R2z; cf. R1j models-vs-infrastructure at p3).
- How climate finance became politically binding — name the institutional/legal mechanisms (R2ad).
- $100bn provenance ("not derived from any economic model") documented precisely; Copenhagen context; the "$100bn anecdotal vs US defense $1.5T" provocation — address scale.
- Rio markers role/functioning (reporting context, by whom, purpose); UNFCCC reporting (to whom/by whom/purpose); donor vs recipient competing measurement regimes; OECD expert groups "set terms of debate" (when/where/who/methods/debates); accountability-vocabulary crystallisation examples; §2.3 more sources.
- Performativity argument: make explanatory not declarative; unpack apparatus/methodologies/consequences (p12).
- p16 UN Advisory Group composition (finance ministers, economists, central bankers, no climate scientists) — reflect on whether it matters.
- Connect the Desrosières quote (p7) to the empirical case.

## Exit criteria
- [ ] Each flagged passage revised with concrete actors/dates/mechanisms; tracked in the cover-letter traceability table
